The paper deals with a wiretap channel model and proposes new lower and upper bounds on the secure degrees of freedom. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of multiple antennas and interference alignment techniques, which are commonly studied in the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the compound private broadcast channel, which involves the transmission of messages to multiple groups, and hence could be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
